Peak check

Sanne

27/01/2020

Generate datasets

Set variables

N <- 1000 # Sample size
p <- 1000 # Number of X variables
q <- 7 # Number of Y variables
K <- 50 # Number of bootstrapping iterations
r <- 3 # Number of joint components
rx <- 3 # Number of specific components of X
ry <- 4 # Number of specific components of Y

Generate parameters

params <- PO2PLS:::generate_params(p, q, r, rx, ry, type = "unit")

# Check standard deviations:
apply(params$W, 2, sd)
## [1] 0.02324630 0.02875617 0.03012772
# Change parameters for different datasets
# Dataset 1: No joint components
params1 <- params
params1$W <- matrix(rnorm(p*r,0,0.005), ncol=r)
params1$C <- matrix(rnorm(q*r,0,0.005), ncol=r)

# Dataset 2: No joint component in first peak, 3x bigger joint component in small area
params2 <- params
params2$W[241:280] <- rnorm(40, 0,0.005)
params2$W[611:650, 1] <- params2$W[611:650, 1]*2

# Peak check: peaks between 240-280 and 520-560
# Create new variable, store mean and variance
params1_p <- params1
params2_p <- params2

# Parameters sorted from high to low, so sample to mix
for(i in 1:rx){
  params1_p$Wo[,i] <- params1_p$Wo[sample.int(N, N), i]
  params2_p$Wo[,i] <- params2_p$Wo[sample.int(N, N), i]
}

# Create peaks in both datasets, with varying peak height
params1_p$Wo[241:280, 1] <- rnorm(40, mean=mean(params1_p$Wo[241:280, 1]), 
                                  sd=sd(params1_p$Wo[241:280, 1])*10)
params1_p$Wo[521:560, 1] <- rnorm(40, mean=mean(params1_p$Wo[521:560, 1]), 
                                  sd=sd(params1_p$Wo[521:560, 1])*3)
params1_p$Wo[431:470, 2] <- rnorm(40, mean=mean(params1_p$Wo[431:470, 1]), 
                                 sd=sd(params1_p$Wo[431:470, 2])*7)
params1_p$Wo[841:880, 3] <- rnorm(40, mean=mean(params1_p$Wo[841:880, 1]), 
                                  sd=sd(params1_p$Wo[841:880, 3])*4)
params2_p$Wo[241:280, 1] <- rnorm(40, mean=mean(params2_p$Wo[241:280, 1]), 
                                  sd=sd(params2_p$Wo[241:280, 1])*10)
params2_p$Wo[521:560, 1] <- rnorm(40, mean=mean(params2_p$Wo[521:560, 1]), 
                                  sd=sd(params2_p$Wo[521:560, 1])*3)
params2_p$Wo[431:470, 2] <- rnorm(40, mean=mean(params2_p$Wo[431:470, 1]), 
                                  sd=sd(params2_p$Wo[431:470, 2])*7)
params2_p$Wo[841:880, 3] <- rnorm(40, mean=mean(params2_p$Wo[841:880, 1]), 
                                  sd=sd(params2_p$Wo[841:880, 3])*4)

Create datasets

data1 <- PO2PLS:::generate_data(100, params1_p)
x1 <- data1[,1:1000]
y1 <- data1[,1001:1007]
data2 <- PO2PLS:::generate_data(100, params2_p)
x2 <- data2[,1:1000]
y2 <- data2[,1001:1007]

Run PO2PLS

No_cor <- PO2PLS(x1, y1, r, rx, ry, init_param = params1_p, steps = 5000)

Results

Joint components

plot(No_cor$params$W[,1], main = "No joint, W-1")

plot(Yes_cor$params$W[,1], main = "Joint, W-1")

plot(No_cor$params$W[,2], main = "No joint, W-2")

Orthogonal components
